widgets_values:
This group creates the brownish background for the icon.

Shouldn't need any tweaking normally

Here the line art for inside the icon is beeing generated.

This part could be much improved, for now it uses a simple Canny line detection.

It then colorizes and masks the lineart for later comping.

Play with the Canny thresholds to get more or less line art

This group creates the thick outline around the icon.

If the thickness of the outline seems off, there's probably something wrong with the scale, check "Desired Larger Side" setting in the input group.

Tweak ThresholdMask if the edges of the icon are janky
This group calculates the dimensions of the final image based on the padding and the "desired larger side" in the Input group

Official sizes for quick comparison:

GUNS (width in pixels)
M18 -> 140
MP5k -> 156
1911 -> 168
PPK -> 188
M4 -> 360
AKM -> 420
M16A4 -> 436
Dragunov -> 464
M240 -> 472
MK17 LB -> 480

OTHER
Frag Grenade -> 144 px (h)

This group prepares the image for further processing.

It will remove the background, crop the image and add a padding on all sides to leave room for the outline later.

Parameters you might want to tweak:

- "Model" in "Remove Background (RMBG)" for difficult backgrounds
- "Sigma" in "Image Sharpen" for unsharp source pictures

Run image through here to flip orientation.

Guns should point to the right
